<paragraph blockId="56.[151,1436,973,1177]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
Comments: The type-series of this species is labeled “ 
<collectingCountry box="[805,876,1045,1069]" name="Brazil" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Brèsil</collectingCountry>
” and “ 
<collectingCountry box="[952,1060,1045,1069]" name="Brazil" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Brasilien</collectingCountry>
,” and no distributional details are known concerning it. Hungerford (1934) expressed doubts concerning the existence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fieber" authorityYear="1851" box="[1133,1227,1082,1105]" class="Insecta" family="Notonectidae" genus="Notonecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis box="[1133,1227,1082,1105]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">N. nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the authenticity of the labels, since he examined many 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[625,740,1118,1141]" class="Insecta" family="Notonectidae" genus="Notonecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[625,740,1118,1141]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Notonecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from various places in 
<collectingCountry box="[1006,1077,1117,1141]" name="Brazil" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, but none seemed to be a representative of this species.
</paragraph>
